<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-05T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/604: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-05T19:00:00-04:00">August 5,
                                    1942—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>192. Your 243, July 24, 6 p.m. War Department requested Colonel Wood to
                            submit recommendations regarding contents of your 243, July 24, 6 p.m.
                            In his reply Wood questioned the need of establishing a defense area at
                            Cape Palmas but made no reference to any approach by the British on the
                            subject of sending radio personnel to that district.</p>
                        <p>Please confer with Wood and report exact nature of British inquiry and
                            reply made thereto. War Department appears to have no present intention
                            of taking over Cape Palmas for defense purposes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>